					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Wobble Eebodee's guide to a Troll Shaman</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:pm5k113@hotmail.com">Wobble Eebodee</a> | 
		            2/28/2001 5:49:46 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Wub Up Trollz?<BR>
 Hey this is a guide made for shamans, but more specifically troll shamans.  I won't go over character creation, find that somewhere else, what I will go over is where to hunt and how to do it.  <BR>
1-4<BR>
 This should be painfully obvious on where to hunt.  Innothule Swamp is a great newbie ground.  Check out the couple of quests that are available to you and keep your eye out for the decayed skellies w/ weapons.  Make sure to use your Inner Fire spell as a heal instead of your heal spell and try not to use your DD too much.  Best if you save the DD for pulls and runners.<BR>
5-8<BR>
  Around 5 I headed to North Ro, most of my friends are good and hang out near FP.  So I killed Coyotes and Jackals in the green part of North Ro.  You got Marissa Sandwhisper right there to sell to you.  Try and remember to grab your L5 spells before you head out and practice channeling before you go too.  Fight the coyotes and jackals then move up to orc raiders.  Just a reminder your KOS to the guards if your a Shammy Troll.  I was using a 2hb at this time, but I would suggest trying to get a piercer as early as possible.  If you can get FS or Velium spear then you'll be fine.  <BR>
8-12<BR>
 You should have just gotten med and your about to get SOW.  If your ever low on money just head to the EC tunnel and SOW for awhile.  I recommend asking politely for donations but not requiring them.  If you haven't gotten your piercer yet you really need to start looking, you'll fall behind (like I did) and have to spend large sums of money to catch it up.  Work on fighting scarabs in EC, lionesses and, if you can find a group, some orcs.  If you find a good group of people make sure to throw them on your friends list to work with in the future.  Try to save your money for spells, they cost a, or so it seems.<BR>
12-13<BR>
 Fight YK's with a group if you can and these levels should go pretty fast.  If you are hunting Young Kodiaks (YKs) then go to WC their more common there.  Just keep an eye out for the guards at tollbooth and also if they just wandered around (Cause someone was pullin' em and they got killed or something similar).<BR>
13-17<BR>
 These not normally controversial levels.  Most people think &quot;Hey time for Derv groups&quot;.  Personally I moaned when I thought of this.  No variety and always shouting for groups.  As an alternative (Which I recommend) head for the sirens in OOT.  For a Troll shaman this is tricky and your gonna wanna pay attention if this is the path your taking.  First off your KOS in FP.. no problem thats fixable.  Go into E FP (the FP zone with the Docks) and go outside the gate into city.  Follow the wall your facing to the left into a corner.  One of the corners will be an invisble wall that you can walk through.  Go through and take the first right in the tunnel.  Go straight through and you'll come to the rogue guild.  Go up and through the stair way and you'll come out in a FP bar basement.  Go up and out and wait near Brunar Starkin (or whatever the Barbarian with the fishing pole) Don't go on the dock!... (If you wait at the dock a humie on the end of the dock with a fishing pole will aggro on and you and the other NPC's will attack as well).  When the boat shows make sure your SOW and make a run for it.  If you don't want to risk it or there is a guard present then your going to have to jump in the water and swim into the front of the boat while its moving toward you.  This is good to practice you'll need to know how to do it later to get off the Siren Islands.  Get on the boat run up to the top cabin and sit against the back wall.  If you sit too far forward the lady at the dock on the Sister Isle will Agro on you and your corpse will be floating around in the ocean (Bad Bad Bad thing to have happen).  After the sister isle go up to the front of the boat and keep an eye out from some grey rocks jutting out of the water.  There should be one set on the left and one set on the right.  Jump off the boat before the rocks and swim to the left rock.  There your going to swim around to the back side of it where a lone siren sits.  Camp that siren and make sure you keep her from running.  If you have to chase her up the rocks the Aqua goblins will aggro on you (Note: you can kill them to gain faction with the Storm guard [Kaladim Faction I think]).  Solo the Siren for as long as it takes to get to 14.  At 14 your going to switch rocks and swim to the other set (the one that was on the right as you came in on the boat).  Now swim over there and med up to full w/ full life.  If you haven't gone and gotten your new spells make sure you have em.  Breaking the spawn is tricky.  If you have someone else there ask for assistence.  If they already broke the spawn then your in luck.  What I did to break the spawn (and was fairly successful doing) was rooting one and using Spirit Strike on the other.  The idea is to immobilize one and kill the other as quickly as possible.  1 at a time they should be a cinch, you should be able to melee the 2nd siren after applying DOTs.  (NOTE: its good to be able to bind out here.  Running through FP is a pain in the butt.  If you want you can solo caimen at 13 and then go out to Siren Island after you have bind affinity)Hopefully this will get you to 16 or 17. If Dervs are your thing and thats what you wanna do then by all means go dervs.<BR>
16-17<BR>
 This is another key decision. High Hold Orcs or Gorge Hounds in EK?  If you can find a partner to kill Gorge Hounds with you in EK (I did it near the Minotaur Gorge zone) then you'll get exp faster.  But you will not get the HH faction.  I chose to kill Gorge Hounds till 17 and then hunt in HH.  By the time I was done I was dubious in HH.  In HH make sure you have your party sit back close away from orc mtn and have a warrior or something pull to the group.  Otherwise trains will start and thats never good.  If you stay and hunt Gorge hounds instead of HH you'll level faster (I can almost guarantee it).  I, (slightly twinked) made sure the group at HH 4 orcs did money split and I asked only for the scalps.  When I Was finally dubious I would disband and do the quest (4 scalps all divided up to the captian Ashlen).  It helps FP faction slightly. Pick up Ringmail Armor from the orcs if you need it.  Its very heavy, but hell its free right?<BR>
19-21<BR>
 At 19 I made the trip to Lake Rathe where I hunted Aviaks with friends.  If you can't find a group there is a solo aviak who you can hunt.  I'm not sure of the lock so ask around.  At 20 I got a friend and we camped the hermit in SK. The hermit is at -5500, -2500 I believe.  If you need to sell (which you will if you get the FS weps) ask for the loc on the centaur village.  They will con indiff and sell to you.  For the Hermit you should rest outside the fort and only go inside to pull.  Keep your eyes peeled for the Tesch Mas gnoll who wanders through occassionally.  As for fighting ranger/hermit is easy.  Use Root w/ DOTS to hold him off. Affliction, Tainted Breath, Sicken.  After these are on turn and run.  When he's decently far away med.  When you see root break stand up and root again.  Reapply DOTs as needed.  When he looks pretty dead go ahead and melee.  If he gets into close while your kiting just melee and time your root in between his swings.  By now you NEED to have a piercer if you haven't your behind.  Pick up something (hopefully you'll have a fairly decent one). <BR>
21-24<BR>
Another major decision.  You can stay at hermit till 23 probably, but I didn't.  My friends and I headed to kunark at 21.  To get to Kunark take the boat in Oasis to the Ogre Oasis.  Switch boats, head to OT.  Bind in city and come back to everlore to download the map.  Find your way to Frontier Mountians, then to Lake of Ill Omen.  Now this is where I'm at (23 1 y from 24).  Sarnaks are definitely your best bet.  Hope you got a nice ISP because the zone will be packed if your server is anything like Xev.  If you can't find a group, form a group.  Your gonna be in demand as a healer most of the time.  Recruits and Adherents are gonna be your mainstay of exp at these levels.  If your group is all under 22 then you probably want to stay outside.  An Enchanter and a power tank are key components to being successful.  If your in a group use str buffs and turtle shell on the tanks.  Healing will probably be your sole duty.  Around 23 or 24 you should try and get into groups that are on &quot;the ledge&quot; (an area on the right side of the coming in that is fairly safe for pulling).  Or across from the the ledge on the other side of the ramp.  The secret to levelling in Lake of Ill Omen is not dying.  I die once a group.  It almost always happens even with the best of groups.  I just make sure that I come out with more exp than I went in with. (Oh yeah, useful note, if you haven't found better pick up a Iksar Skull Helm here, 5ac +3wis, No Drop. They work well).  Hopefully by the time your 24 you have a friend who's willing to make an iksar character, and run in and get your 24 spells.  Thats as far as I've gotten so my level guide ends there.<BR>
<BR>
The Art of Soloing<BR>
 Yes Soloing is an art.  Most people think, wow Shammy he just kites.  Well they are somewhat correct.  If your soloing your not doing it druid style would be my guess.  Your mana will puss out on you too fast and since you can't snare they won't give you any signifigant amount of time to med and rejuvinate your mana.  Before I solo (I'm now at 23) I always Spirit Str, Frenzy, Inner Fire, Turtle Shell and then med to FM.  I start off with root then Affliction (sometimes interchanged with malise at the front)Tainted Breath, and sicken if I have the extra slot.  I follow up with a walking sleep if I have the mana (you should be at about half mana now).  Step back so that you have enough time to cast a new root should your old one break.  Med until your little yellow text &quot;your root breaks&quot; then reapply.  Hopefully you'll be able to reroot, scoot back and then reapply dot's as needed.  By the time your OOM he's 3/4's dead and thats why you have a 12ft pole with a sticker on end of it.  Thats right, you melee him to death.  Between frenzy and Spirit Str you should have no problem.  While most classes worry about how much downtime inbetween solo fights you just need to worry about staying alive.  <BR>
<BR>
The Art of Group fighting<BR>
 Your going to need a group eventually (except when you get pet, or so I hear).  In a group you should find out what is needed.  Sometimes you'll get grouped with a higher level shammy.  I recommend letting him do the DOT's and Debuffs and you do the Buffs and Healing, the exception would be if he has a better healing spell, then you might reconsider.<BR>
 If your the buff/healer save your mana and just melee when the fights pop up.  Keep everyone healed and watch for any MOBs that get really pissed at ya for the healing.  It'll happen, especially with Sarnaks.  If you haven't learned yet understand the mechanics of the Enchanter's AOE mez and regular Mez.  It'll save your group death and death again to understand how it works. Make sure you stay SOWed.  If things get ugly know when to run, sometimes you get a bad group and you see things going rotten before it even happens, tell your group that they need to getting ready to head out cause its lookin' bad.<BR>
  Over time, if your paying attention, you'll know what to look for in a group.  For example fear, if a group is fearing inside the Sarnak Fort then somethings very wrong.  There is no better way to start a train than to have an Iksar running through the fort gathering the recruits and adherents for one big attack.  Another sign is how well the puller knows the area. If the puller knows whats happening then things will go better.  If a group isn't working with an enchanter right, or if they pull too many, if they are situated in the wrong spot for their level, all of these will be intracies that you'll learn when you understand the zone.  Use them to help you get an idea of what kind of success you'll get in working with that group.<BR>
  That pretty much concludes my Shaman guide.  I hope it helps.  There is infinitely more I can tell you, but I think you'll learn it faster on your own anyway.  And remember, its more than a game.  Its a fun game:) so treat it like one.<BR>
<BR>
 If your unclear on something and you wanna send me a tell on the Xev Server feel free.<BR>
<BR>
Wobble Eebodee<BR>
23 (1 yellow from 24) Shaman<BR>
Xev Server
